  "text": "CSS Style Change Propagation through Chromium's Blink Rendering Pipeline:\n\nThe rendering pipeline in Chromium's Blink engine progresses through four key stages:\n\n1. **Style Resolution (StyleResolver)** - File: third_party/blink/renderer/core/css/resolver/style_resolver.h\n   The StyleResolver class (defined at line 63) is responsible for resolving computed styles for DOM elements. It selects a ComputedStyle for a given element based on the document's collection of stylesheets (user styles, author styles, UA style). There is a 1-1 relationship between StyleResolver and Document. This is the entry point where CSS styles are computed and applied to elements.\n\n2. **Layout Tree (LayoutObject)** - File: third_party/blink/renderer/core/layout/layout_object.h\n   The LayoutObject class (defined at line 270) is the base class for the layout tree. It represents a node in the layout tree that corresponds to a DOM element. LayoutObject handles the positioning and sizing of elements based on their computed styles. Child classes of LayoutObject include LayoutBox, LayoutInline, LayoutText, and many specialized layout classes for different content types.\n\n3. **Paint Layers (PaintLayer)** - File: third_party/blink/renderer/core/paint/paint_layer.h\n   The PaintLayer class (defined at line 174) represents the painting layer abstraction. It groups one or more LayoutObjects that paint together. PaintLayers are crucial for implementing complex painting operations (opacity, clipping, filters, reflections), hardware acceleration through compositing, scrolling, and performance optimizations. Not all LayoutObjects have a corresponding PaintLayer - only those that require special treatment for painting purposes.\n\n4. **Display List Recording (PaintController + DisplayItemList)** - Files: third_party/blink/renderer/platform/graphics/paint/paint_controller.h and third_party/blink/renderer/platform/graphics/paint/display_item_list.h\n   - PaintController (defined at line 131 in paint_controller.h) is responsible for processing display items as they are produced and creating a final paint artifact when complete. It includes logic for caching, cache invalidation, and merging of paint operations.\n   - DisplayItemList (defined at line 28 in display_item_list.h) is a container for a list of display items of various types. It stores the actual paint operations that will be rasterized to pixels.\n\nThe flow progresses: Style (CSS) → Layout (geometry) → Paint Layers (grouping) → Display Items (recording paint operations) → Rasterization. When a CSS style changes, the StyleResolver recomputes styles, which triggers layout recalculation, layer updates, and finally display item recording for the affected elements."
}

